# Implementation Plan: Admin Architecture & Scaffolding

This phase introduces the **Admin** role into the framework. Because the Admin area requires a completely different Sidebar (with "Books Management", "Fines Management") than the User area, we need to adjust our layout strategy.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To support two distinct sidebars without building complex "if/else" logic in a single file, I am proposing we use **Next.js Route Groups** (`(user)` and `(admin)`). 
> 
> *This means I will move all the current routes (`app/page.tsx`, `app/loans`, etc.) into `app/(user)/` and create a new environment under `app/(admin)/`. The user URL paths will NOT change (it's still `/loans`), but the admin URLs will live at `/admin/loans` etc.*

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Route Group Restructuring (Next.js Best Practice)
#### [NEW] `app/(user)/layout.tsx`
- The current `app/layout.tsx` logic (incorporating the User Sidebar) will be moved here.

#### [NEW] `app/(admin)/layout.tsx`
- A unique layout strictly for the `/admin` routes.
- Will mount a brand new `components/admin-sidebar.tsx`.

#### [MODIFY] `app/` Directory
- All current folders (`books`, `fines`, `loans`, `profile`, `reservations`, `settings`, `subscription`, `wishlist`, `page.tsx`) will be safely moved inside `app/(user)/`.

### 2. Admin Sidebar Component
#### [NEW] `components/admin-sidebar.tsx`
- Replicates the persistent glassmorphism 'No-Line' aesthetic of the user sidebar.
- Contains links:
  - Dashboard (`/admin`)
  - Books Mgt (`/admin/books`)
  - Book Loans Mgt (`/admin/loans`)
  - Fines Mgt (`/admin/fines`)
  - Bottom actions: Profile, Settings, Logout.

### 3. Admin Page Scaffolding
#### [NEW] `app/(admin)/admin/page.tsx` (Admin Dashboard)
- Overview metrics: Total Active Users, Total Books, Overdue Revenue.

#### [NEW] `app/(admin)/admin/books/page.tsx` (Books Management)
- ShadCN Table detailing physical/digital inventory, add/edit book actions, stock numbers.

#### [NEW] `app/(admin)/admin/loans/page.tsx` (Book Loans Management)
- Table/Grid managing active checkouts, overdue status forced resolutions.

#### [NEW] `app/(admin)/admin/fines/page.tsx` (Fines Management)
- Global ledger of all user fines, waiving abilities.

